<p>I suffered from #9 a lot when I was younger and still do somewhat.  As others have said though, time helps.</p>

<p>If you&#8217;re flying lots, do yourself a favor and get a mileage card (apply online to avoid imposing on a real person!).  They don&#8217;t cost anything and just by virtue of having one you&#8217;ll get seats with more leg room (United calls them &#8220;Economy Plus&#8221; seats - I&#8217;m assuming all airlines have something similar but YMMV).</p>

